{"questionId":"22499296","questionHtml":"<p>Hence verify that your answer to part (b) is a solution to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi></mrow></msup></mfrac></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>substitution of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math> from part (b) into part(c)(i) or original differential equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>M1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi></mrow></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>and hence <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is a solution for the differential equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Only award the <em><strong>A1</strong></em> as follow-through if their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;is of the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"22499296","referenceCode":"24M.2.AHL.TZ1.5d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence verify that your answer to part (b) is a solution to dydx=xe2y.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.9—Differentiating standard functions and derivative rules"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}